With thunderous cheers and applause, the show comes to an end

169
00:14:53,816 --> 00:14:57,816
↑まあ、これはあくまで理想の話なんですが^^;
↑Well, this is just an ideal story, though... ^^;

170
00:15:12,404 --> 00:15:13,704
さて、今日も始めましょうか…
Now, shall we begin today as well...

171
00:15:14,404 --> 00:15:15,604
あ～！ またやっちゃった～！
Ah! I did it again!

172
00:15:15,904 --> 00:15:19,004
実際はご覧の通り まだまだ未熟な見習いなんです
In reality, as you can see, I'm still just an inexperienced apprentice

173
00:15:19,504 --> 00:15:22,604
先人に憧れ持って 私も！と飛び込んだものの
Admiring my predecessors, I dove right in, saying 'Me too!'

174
00:15:23,004 --> 00:15:25,904
現実はそんな簡単に 上手くいかないなあ…
But reality doesn't go that smoothly...

175
00:15:26,204 --> 00:15:29,704
もういっかい！ 「怪奇模した喜劇が幕開け 一目見ればたちまち虜に！？」
One more time! 'A comedy mimicking the bizarre begins, and one look will make you a captive!?'

176
00:15:29,904 --> 00:15:33,304
え？ 既にそれさっき見たなら なら、飽き性なあなたにも【朗報】
Eh? If you've already seen that just now, then, [Good News] for you who get bored easily

177
00:15:33,504 --> 00:15:35,104
Q. ちょっと前の模倣をするだけ
Q. Just mimicking what happened a bit ago

178
00:15:35,504 --> 00:15:39,004
A. 繰り返しじゃつまらない！ だから、ここから先は趣向を変えてみよう！
A. Repetition is boring! So, from here on, let's change things up!

179
00:16:08,904 --> 00:16:12,404
ドタバタなサーカスの行方は 誰にも自分すらも分からない！？
The outcome of this slapstick circus, nobody knows, not even me!?

180
00:16:12,704 --> 00:16:15,904
私を選んだ君だけでも楽しんでってよ～～～！！！ 損させないから
At least you, who chose me, please enjoy yourself!!! I won't let you down

181
00:16:16,204 --> 00:16:19,404
いつの日か皆と楽しめる ショーがしたいんだよな～！
I want to put on a show one day that everyone can enjoy!

182
00:16:19,604 --> 00:16:22,604
だからこそ、こんなとこで 挫けるわけとかないな～い！
That's exactly why there's no way I'm giving up here!

183
00:16:25,104 --> 00:16:27,604
言葉なんかじゃ言い表せない あの感動を私もいつか…
I can't put it into words, that inspiration... I hope to one day...

184
00:16:27,904 --> 00:16:31,304
とても偉大なこのステージに 見合っているか分かんないけれど
I don't know if I'm worthy of this great stage, but

185
00:16:31,604 --> 00:16:35,004
観客全て、私の色で 染め尽くしてやろう！
I'll dye every single audience member in my own colors!

186
00:16:35,204 --> 00:16:38,304
手始めに、今、眼の前の君たちからいくよ～～～！！！
To start off, I'm coming for you guys right in front of me now!!!

187
00:16:38,604 --> 00:16:42,204
創造しよう 華々しいスポットライトの中 目を奪うような妙技の数々
Let's create, amidst the glorious spotlight, many eye-catching feats

188
00:16:42,404 --> 00:16:46,004
この空間が世界で一番 “享楽”の名に相応しいんだ！
This space is the most fitting in the world for the name 'Pleasure'!

189
00:16:46,204 --> 00:16:49,204
割れんばかりの歓声と拍手で ショーが終わっていく
With thunderous cheers and applause, the show comes to an end

190
00:16:49,404 --> 00:16:52,404
ああ…これが私が望んだ夢のエンディング。
Ah... this is the dream ending I wished for.

191
00:17:30,204 --> 00:17:36,504
これは花の国のお姫様がこの王国へいらっしゃった時のお話
This is a story about when the princess of the flower country came to this kingdom.

192
00:17:36,804 --> 00:17:39,604
まだみんな彼女の事を知らない頃だったので
It was back when nobody knew about her yet,

193
00:17:39,904 --> 00:17:43,204
国民の大半は、アホの子なんて言ってたけど、
so most of the citizens called her an airhead, but...

194
00:17:43,504 --> 00:17:51,204
とっても心優しくそして気さくで頼りになるお姫様だったんだよ
She was a very kind-hearted, friendly, and reliable princess.

195
00:17:51,504 --> 00:17:55,304
なんてったって、みこはお姫様なんだから！
After all, Miko is a princess!

196
00:18:04,304 --> 00:18:05,504
女神！
Goddess!

197
00:18:05,504 --> 00:18:06,404
聖女！
Saint!

198
00:18:06,404 --> 00:18:07,304
叡智！
Wisdom!

199
00:18:07,304 --> 00:18:08,204
聡明！
Brightness!

200
00:18:08,204 --> 00:18:09,204
慈愛！
Benevolence!

201
00:18:09,204 --> 00:18:10,104
博愛！
Philanthropy!

202
00:18:10,104 --> 00:18:11,004
ですわ！
Indeed!

203
00:18:11,104 --> 00:18:13,204
あたし なんてったってお姫様
I'm a princess after all

204
00:18:13,304 --> 00:18:16,304
この人生におけるヒロイン
The heroine of this life

205
00:18:16,404 --> 00:18:17,504
ですわー！
Indeed!

206
00:18:22,404 --> 00:18:24,504
一生 姫プでイージーモード！
Princess-carry easy mode for life!

207
00:18:24,604 --> 00:18:25,504
って思ったら勝手にどうぞ？
If that's what you think, go right ahead?

208
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:27,804
世間はいつも気まぐれ次第
The world is always at its own whims

209
00:18:27,904 --> 00:18:31,104
有象無象ばかりでホント 人間不信になっちゃう！
Full of the common rabble, honestly, I'm losing faith in humanity!

210
00:18:33,504 --> 00:18:38,304
気づいたのこの世界に 血も涙もないことを
I realized that in this world, there's neither blood nor tears

211
00:18:39,004 --> 00:18:43,104
あれもダメ、これもダメ、それもダメ、 どれもダメ、現実は世知辛い！
That's no good, this is no good, that too, none of it, reality is harsh!

212
00:18:43,504 --> 00:18:44,504
改変だ…
It's a reform...

213
00:18:45,404 --> 00:18:47,404
全部改変ですわ…！
It's a total reform...!

214
00:18:48,504 --> 00:18:50,504
あたし なんてったってお姫様
I'm a princess after all

215
00:18:50,604 --> 00:18:53,704
この人生におけるヒロイン
The heroine of this life

216
00:18:54,504 --> 00:18:59,104
悲しいシナリオも全部全部書き換えちゃうの
Even sad scenarios, I'll rewrite them all

217
00:18:59,904 --> 00:19:01,904
だってだって お姫様
Because, after all, I'm a princess

218
00:19:02,104 --> 00:19:05,004
自分の物語くらいは
At the very least, my own story...

219
00:19:05,204 --> 00:19:09,204
キラキラ楽しまなきゃ ですわ！ですわ！ですわ！ですわ！
I have to enjoy it sparklingly! Indeed! Indeed! Indeed! Indeed!

220
00:19:10,504 --> 00:19:11,804
今にみてなさい！
Just you watch!

221
00:19:11,904 --> 00:19:15,604
運命なんて 改変して差し上げますわ！
Destiny? I'll reform it for you!

222
00:19:22,104 --> 00:19:24,504
だれ？ だれ？ だれ？ だれ？
Who? Who? Who? Who?

223
00:19:24,604 --> 00:19:27,804
裏で糸を引いてるのはだれ？
Who is pulling the strings behind the scenes?

224
00:19:27,904 --> 00:19:30,504
操り人形だなんて
Being a puppet...

225
00:19:30,904 --> 00:19:33,304
ごめんだわ まったく
I'm quite done with that

226
00:19:33,404 --> 00:19:36,204
上品な顔してても
Even with an elegant face,

227
00:19:36,304 --> 00:19:39,004
黒幕はあの人かも
That person might be the mastermind

228
00:19:39,204 --> 00:19:41,304
まずはあたしが 強くならなきゃ
First, I have to become stronger

229
00:19:41,504 --> 00:19:43,204
未来は変わらない
Future won't change

230
00:19:43,304 --> 00:19:44,504
改革だ…
It's a revolution...

231
00:19:45,404 --> 00:19:47,404
自分改革ですわ…！
It's a self-revolution...!

232
00:19:48,404 --> 00:19:50,504
そうよ なんてったってお姫様
That's right, I'm a princess after all

233
00:19:50,604 --> 00:19:53,704
あたしこそ最高権力者
I am the supreme ruler

234
00:19:54,404 --> 00:19:59,104
生涯のすべての主導権はこちらにあるわ
The initiative for all of my life lies here

235
00:19:59,904 --> 00:20:01,904
だってだって お姫様
Because, after all, I'm a princess

236
00:20:02,104 --> 00:20:05,004
自分で決めたことくらいは
At least the things I decided for myself...

237
00:22:29,845 --> 00:22:31,945
暗澹たるストーリーライン
A bleak storyline,

238
00:22:31,945 --> 00:22:35,545
難攻不落と化しちゃえ
becoming an impregnable fortress.

239
00:22:35,745 --> 00:22:38,945
アクロイドとされた探偵が
The detective who was made out as Ackroyd...

240
00:22:39,045 --> 00:22:42,445
また一人姿を消したと言う
is said to have vanished once again.

241
00:22:42,745 --> 00:22:45,145
綾なす辻のアリスがわ
Alice in the weaving crossroads,

242
00:22:45,145 --> 00:22:49,545
横溝正史は江戸川か
Is Seishi Yokomizo or Edogawa next?

243
00:22:49,745 --> 00:22:53,045
神田最弱探偵さん
The weakest detective of Kanda,

244
00:22:53,045 --> 00:22:56,245
こんなんどう居ると思う？
how do you think they'll fare?

245
00:22:56,945 --> 00:22:59,345
南無阿弥陀仏 ステップ
Namu Amida Butsu Step,

246
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:03,445
脳髄是れ密室なりや
Is the brain itself a locked room?

247
00:23:03,845 --> 00:23:05,345
偶然会った人
The person met by chance,

248
00:23:05,345 --> 00:23:06,845
偶然別れましょう
let us part by chance.

249
00:23:06,845 --> 00:23:08,945
謎解きはこれから
The mystery-solving starts now.

250
00:23:09,845 --> 00:23:12,145
「犯人はあなたですわ」
"The culprit is you!"

251
00:23:12,145 --> 00:23:15,245
連続 密室 発火トリック 殺人事件
Serial, locked-room, fire-trick murder case.

252
00:23:15,545 --> 00:23:18,245
推理作家の先生さん
The mystery writer, Sensei-san.

253
00:23:18,245 --> 00:23:18,945
あははは！
Ahahaha!

254
00:23:18,945 --> 00:23:22,245
うだるパズル うだるパズル いまだに出逢えず
Boiling puzzles, boiling puzzles, yet to meet...

255
00:23:22,245 --> 00:23:25,345
ああもう、頭がこんがらがってきたけれど
Ah geez, my head is getting all tangled up, but...

256
00:23:25,745 --> 00:23:29,045
ドトハライ・ドットコム あちゃちゃちゃパリパリ
Dotobarai dot com, achachacha pari-pari,

257
00:23:29,045 --> 00:23:30,845
エブリバディわんこそば
Everybody, Wanko Soba.

258
00:23:30,845 --> 00:23:32,445
「謎はおやつに入りません」
"Mysteries aren't included as snacks."

259
00:23:32,545 --> 00:23:35,945
ドトハライ・ドットコム あちゃちゃちゃドンシャリ
Dotobarai dot com, achachacha don-shari,

260
00:23:35,945 --> 00:23:37,845
エブリバディあばいばい
Everybody, bye-bye,

261
00:23:37,845 --> 00:23:40,145
ない、ない、ない
nothing, nothing, nothing.

262
00:23:53,545 --> 00:23:56,045
エキセントリック大変馬鹿げた末路に
To an eccentric, greatly foolish end,

263
00:23:56,045 --> 00:23:59,345
万歳三唱 続いてご清聴
three cheers, and thanks for listening.

264
00:23:59,545 --> 00:24:02,945
オリエント急行客車の窓
The window of the Orient Express,

265
00:24:03,045 --> 00:24:06,445
あの怪盗たちが笑うと言う
it's said those phantom thieves are laughing.

266
00:24:06,745 --> 00:24:09,045
黄昏に二人海原
Two people in the twilight ocean,

267
00:24:09,045 --> 00:24:13,245
坂口安吾 無視したろ
Ango Sakaguchi, you ignored it, right?

268
00:24:13,545 --> 00:24:16,845
ABCだかエビスだか
ABC or Ebisu or whatever,

269
00:24:16,845 --> 00:24:20,245
レモンドちゃんとしてして
Raymond, do it properly.

270
00:24:20,845 --> 00:24:23,545
甲が乙を隠す
A hides B,

271
00:24:24,045 --> 00:24:27,245
そんじょ隆参戦さん お疲れさん
well then, Takashi-san joins the fray, good work.

272
00:24:27,745 --> 00:24:29,245
四捨五入してみな
Try rounding it off,

273
00:24:29,245 --> 00:24:30,845
死者五人どこ行った？
where did the five victims go?

274
00:24:30,845 --> 00:24:33,945
謎解きはまだまだ
The mystery-solving is far from over.

275
00:24:34,845 --> 00:24:36,445
「そして誰もいなくなったわ」
"And then there were none."

276
00:24:36,445 --> 00:24:39,545
およしになって おやめになって 怪事件
Please stop, please cease, this strange case.

277
00:24:39,745 --> 00:24:42,945
お下げ揺らす 探偵さん
Swinging her pigtails, the detective-san.

278
00:24:42,945 --> 00:24:43,545
探偵さん！
Detective-san!

279
00:24:43,545 --> 00:24:46,945
ノックスべべ ガストンべべ いかないで、ああもう
Knox baby, Gaston baby, don't go, ah geez...

280
00:24:46,945 --> 00:24:50,045
先生の意地悪は毎度
Sensei's meanness is a constant.

281
00:24:50,545 --> 00:24:53,745
ドトハライ・ドットコム あちゃちゃちゃパリパリ
Dotobarai dot com, achachacha pari-pari,

282
00:24:53,745 --> 00:24:55,245
エブリバディわんこそば
Everybody, Wanko Soba.

283
00:24:55,245 --> 00:24:56,945
「たまには自分で考えたまえ」
"Try thinking for yourself once in a while."

284
00:24:57,045 --> 00:25:00,445
ドトハライ・ドットコム あちゃちゃちゃドンシャリ
Dotobarai dot com, achachacha don-shari.

285
00:25:00,353 --> 00:25:01,653
エブリバディ
Everybody

286
00:25:01,653 --> 00:25:02,853
アリバイ
Alibi

287
00:25:02,853 --> 00:25:04,353
ナイ ナイ ナイ ナイ
None, none, none, none

288
00:25:17,653 --> 00:25:19,753
怪盗の目の 穴にはまり
Falling into the trap of the phantom thief's eyes,

289
00:25:19,753 --> 00:25:22,153
次々と 姿を消していく
one after another they disappear,

290
00:25:22,153 --> 00:25:24,053
名探偵たち
the great detectives.

291
00:25:24,753 --> 00:25:27,053
そして 探偵の居ぬ間に
And while the detective is away,

292
00:25:27,053 --> 00:25:29,553
人々の心は 密室となった
people's hearts became locked rooms.

293
00:25:32,753 --> 00:25:36,853
「でも、それならどうしてあたしだけが無事だったんでしょうか？」
"But then why was I the only one who was safe?"

294
00:25:37,353 --> 00:25:39,053
「その答えはひとつしか考えられない」
"There can only be one answer to that."

295
00:25:40,353 --> 00:25:41,853
「と、云うと……？」
"Which is...?"

296
00:25:42,653 --> 00:25:45,353
「あまりに無能すぎるが故に、」
"Because you are too incompetent,"

297
00:25:45,353 --> 00:25:48,653
「きみは探偵として勘定にも入れられていなかったのだ!」
"you weren't even counted as a detective!"

298
00:25:48,653 --> 00:25:50,353
「いーやー!」
"Nooo!"

299
00:25:51,653 --> 00:25:54,953
およしになって おやめになって 怪奇事件
Please stop, please quit this mysterious case.

300
00:25:55,153 --> 00:25:57,453
おさげ揺らす 探偵さん
The detective shaking her pigtails,

301
00:25:57,453 --> 00:25:58,553
『探偵さん!』
"Detective!"

302
00:25:59,153 --> 00:26:02,453
Knock's baby, Got it's baby, 行かないで
Knock's baby, Got it's baby, don't go.

303
00:26:02,453 --> 00:26:05,053
a-m-o-r 先生の 意地悪イケズ
A-M-O-R, Professor's mean trick.

304
00:26:05,453 --> 00:26:07,353
ロードショートリック ハットトリック
Roadshow trick, hat trick,

305
00:26:07,353 --> 00:26:08,853
難事件
it's a difficult case.

306
00:26:08,853 --> 00:26:12,053
推理作家の先生
The mystery writer professor.

307
00:26:12,653 --> 00:26:14,953
うだらうだら 言わないで
Don't just mumble on and on.

308
00:26:14,953 --> 00:26:19,153
あぁもう 頭がこんがらがってきたけど
Ah, my head is getting all tangled up, but...

309
00:26:19,653 --> 00:26:21,353
来いよ来いよ トリック
Come on, come on, trick,

310
00:26:21,353 --> 00:26:23,053
甘い接待
sweet entertainment.

311
00:26:23,053 --> 00:26:25,853
通りゃんせ
Toryanse.

312
00:26:40,353 --> 00:26:43,353
小さい2人の子供が約束した、
Two small children made a promise,

313
00:26:43,353 --> 00:26:47,053
ずっといっしょに笑っていようの約束。
a promise to always laugh together.

314
00:26:47,653 --> 00:26:51,853
今もなお、2人の絆は確かなもので
Even now, the bond between the two is certain,

315
00:26:51,853 --> 00:26:56,853
友情と愛情が織りなす素敵な物語。
a wonderful story woven with friendship and love.

316
00:26:57,653 --> 00:27:03,353
「あははっ…なんでもないことに、妙にツボっちゃう時あるよねっ」
"Ahaha... there are times when you just strangely crack up at nothing, right?"

317
00:27:15,853 --> 00:27:19,153
あぁ 恋に落ち たまゆら 開花 止まらないや
Ah, the fleeting moment I fell in love, the blooming won't stop.

318
00:27:19,453 --> 00:27:22,653
何度も捲って 心をかし
Flipping through it again and again, the heart is interesting.

319
00:27:23,353 --> 00:27:26,453
泣いてばっかだったの それがどうだ今や
I was always crying, but what about now?

320
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:30,153
腹捩るくらい笑う
I laugh until my sides hurt.

321
00:27:30,653 --> 00:27:34,053
ずっと一緒に笑って 心をかし
Always laughing together, the heart is interesting.

322
00:27:34,053 --> 00:27:35,853
ずっと一緒に笑う
Always laughing together.

323
00:27:35,853 --> 00:27:37,653
最後の日を笑う
Laughing on the last day.

324
00:27:37,653 --> 00:27:41,053
きみが持ってる 白い花に
In the white flower you hold,

325
00:27:41,053 --> 00:27:44,553
あたし見合わない 悲しくなる
I don't fit, it makes me sad.

326
00:27:44,553 --> 00:27:48,053
無垢な恋とか 正しさとか
Innocent love or righteousness,

327
00:27:48,053 --> 00:27:51,653
誰も教えてくれなかった
no one taught me either.

328
00:27:52,353 --> 00:27:55,553
昨日会ったばっかで 今日またどっか会えたら
I met you just yesterday, if I could meet you somewhere today,

329
00:27:55,553 --> 00:27:59,053
なんて思う暮らし 慎ましいくらいよね
what a way to live, thinking that. It's quite humble, isn't it?

330
00:27:59,353 --> 00:28:01,353
全部許されたの
Everything was forgiven.

331
00:28:01,353 --> 00:28:03,053
びっくりしちゃってさ
I was surprised,

332
00:28:03,053 --> 00:28:05,553
涙あふれてたよ
tears were overflowing.

333
00:28:07,853 --> 00:28:10,853
もう愛になる花歌 透き通った空
The flower song that is now love, the clear sky.

334
00:28:11,153 --> 00:28:14,853
手をつないでた 夢のしるし
Hand in hand, a sign of a dream.

335
